They shouldn’t offer veggie burgers. I realize it’s silly going to burger place when you’re vegan/vegetarian but hey, it’s nice to have options. When I got there, they assured me all of the ingredients they had were vegan. However, they didn’t change utensils or gloves before preparing my order. And better yet, the grill was not cleaned, and there is no separate area for veggie burgers. My patty was touching a beef one. If you’re going to offer vegan options, cross contamination is something that goes along with that promise, and I specifically sought out this restaurant because of the website advertising “veggie” patties. I just think this company needs to be a little more aware of what a claim like that means. Otherwise, just stick to beef, which is fine. I feel bad for anyone who ordered mobile thinking they were receiving the same standards of preparation most other companies live by.

This is a 5 star burger joint - best burger I've ever had and I've traveled a lot! - but a 2 star staff. Could be nationwide if they would train staff better.  Owner, manager... are you listening? I've been to each of your locations and love your food. I savor getting a burger at your place every time, then I have to deal with your staff. I have eaten at Relish over a dozen times. I have had a pleasant interaction with staff once. The first time I came in I almost walked out in anger because of unprofessional staffing. Once I brought a group and had to apologize for the poor customer care but they still enjoyed the food.  Team members are often in back talking and seem to sigh when  customers come in. On more then one occasion I've been corrected when ordering - I don't think this is a great way to feel welcomed. In general the impression I get is the people working at Relish don't want to be there.  I love your place and think it is doing well despite poor staff training. Imagine if you took your product and combined it with a quality customer experience? You would be a nationwide franchise. I think of Chick Fil A, not great food, but such good customer service you don't really care.  I recommend Relish to everyone, for the food, just be ready for curt, unprofessional, unfriendly staff.
